# SynapseOS — Windsurf Rules

## Project
SynapseOS: self-improving BYOK RAG platform with cognitive engine.
Deploy: Oracle ARM A1 (4 vCPU / 24GB RAM, NO GPU) via Coolify.

## Stack (locked — never suggest alternatives)
FastAPI | Qdrant 1.13.5 | fastembed bge-base-en-v1.5 768d |
LiteLLM → Groq → OpenRouter → Anthropic |
mem0ai | Crawl4AI | Docling | RAGAS | DSPy | Langfuse |
KeyDB | MinIO | FastMCP | Cloudflare Workers

## ARM Rules (non-negotiable)
- OMP_NUM_THREADS=4 always before fastembed import
- batch_size=64 ingestion, 16 query
- Cross-encoder: max 15 docs input
- KeyDB: AOF only, NO RDB (save "")
- Qdrant: on_disk=True, memmap_threshold_kb=50000
- Docling: concurrency=1, DOCLING_CPU_ONLY=1

## Code Requirements
- All async — no sync blocking in FastAPI
- Complete files only — never partial code or ellipsis
- All imports explicit at top
- Type hints required
- API keys from os.environ only
- Fernet encryption for BYOK tenant keys
- tenant_id filter on every Qdrant query

## Collections
synapse_knowledge = RAG | synapse_memory = mem0

